bHostMIB.name: bHostMIB

revisions.description: Changed bSysTotalMem, bSysMemUsed and bSysMemFree from CounterBasedGauge64 to Unsigned32
Improved the use of 64 Bit Gauge by replacing Unsigned64 with CounterBasedGauge64
Updated notification assignments to comply with standards (RFC 2578).
Updated MIB file with change in MAX-ACCESS level for notification objects.
updated MIB file with change in bHostNotifObjects
Changed bSWTaskRunStateTime from Unsigned32 to TimeTicks

bHostMIBObjects.description: MIB objects for Host related statistics are defined in this branch.

bHostNotifObjects.name: bHostNotifObjects
bHostNotifObjects.description: Notifications of Host related statistics are defined in this branch.

bHostNotifVariables.name: bHostNotifVariables
bHostNotifVariables.description: MIB objects for Host notifications are defined in this branch.

bSWTaskInfoTable.name: bSWTaskInfoTable
bSWTaskInfoTable.description: The (conceptual) table of running software performance metrics.

bSWTaskInfoEntry.name: bSWTaskInfoEntry
bSWTaskInfoEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry containing software performance metrics.

bSWTaskIndex.name: bSWTaskIndex
bSWTaskIndex.description: Index of the software task entry in the table.

bSWTaskName.name: bSWTaskName
bSWTaskName.description: The name of the running software task.

bSWTaskRunStateTime.name: bSWTaskRunStateTime
bSWTaskRunStateTime.description: The amount of CPU time used by the process since it is started. Value will be in hundredths of a second

bSWTaskCPUUsage.name: bSWTaskCPUUsage
bSWTaskCPUUsage.description: CPU usage of the task in the last 1 sec interval duration. The task share of the elapsed time as a percentage of total CPU time is recorded for one second. Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to maxcore*100

bSWTaskAvgCPUUsage.name: bSWTaskAvgCPUUsage
bSWTaskAvgCPUUsage.description: Average CPU usage of the task in the last load interval duration. The task share of the elapsed time as a percentage of total CPU time is recorded for every one second.These one second samples are averaged over a period of load interval.After every one second, older one sec sample will be discarded and new sample will be added to the set . After addition of a new sample value , average over one second samples in a interval will be done. Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to maxcore*100

bSWTaskMaxCPUUsage.name: bSWTaskMaxCPUUsage
bSWTaskMaxCPUUsage.description: Maximum CPU usage of the task in the last load interval duration. The task share of the elapsed time as a percentage of total CPU time is recorded for every one second. The maximum of these one second samples is calculated over a period of load interval duration. This counter enable to detect the spikes in cpu usage . After every one second, older one sec sample will be discarded and new sample will be added to the set . After addition of new sample value , maximum value over one second intervals in a interval duration will be calculated . Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to maxcore*100

bSWTaskCodeSegmentSize.name: bSWTaskCodeSegmentSize
bSWTaskCodeSegmentSize.description: Code segment size of the process. Units kilo-bytes

bSWTaskDataSegmentSize.name: bSWTaskDataSegmentSize
bSWTaskDataSegmentSize.description: Data segment size of the process. Units kilo-bytes

bSWTaskResidentPhyMem.name: bSWTaskResidentPhyMem
bSWTaskResidentPhyMem.description: The non-swapped physical memory a task has used. Units kilo-bytes

bSWTaskVirtMemUsage.name: bSWTaskVirtMemUsage
bSWTaskVirtMemUsage.description: The total amount of virtual memory used by the task. Units kilo-bytes

bSWTaskSharedMem.name: bSWTaskSharedMem
bSWTaskSharedMem.description: The amount of shared memory used by a task. Units kilo-bytes

bSWTaskVirtMemPeakUsage.name: bSWTaskVirtMemPeakUsage
bSWTaskVirtMemPeakUsage.description: The peak usage of total amount of virtual memory used by the task. Units kilo-bytes

bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold.name: bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold
bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold.description: The high threshold for average cpu utilization of a task in a load interval. If a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow event has been generated ( or no bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh was generated previously ) for this task, and the value for average cpu utilization has exceeded the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold, then a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh event will be generated. No more bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh events will be generated for this task until the value for average cpu utilization becomes equal to or less than the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold. Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to bSWTaskCPUUsageLimit

bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold.name: bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold
bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold.description: The low threshold for avaerage cpu utilization of a task in a load interval. If a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh event has been generated ( or no bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow was generated previously ) for this task, and the value for average cpu utilization has fallen below the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold, then a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow event will be generated. No more bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow events will be generated for this task until the value for average cpu utilization exceeds the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold. Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold

bSWTaskCPUUsageLimit.name: bSWTaskCPUUsageLimit
bSWTaskCPUUsageLimit.description: The limit on cpu usage of the process.When cpu usage of a process reaches this limit , process would be killed and bSWTaskDied notification will be sent. The reason in this notification would be cpuUsageLimitReached . Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to maxcore*100

bSWTaskRestartLimit.name: bSWTaskRestartLimit
bSWTaskRestartLimit.description: The limit on restart of the process.When bSWTaskRestartCount of a process reaches this limit , process would not be restarted and bSWTaskRestartLimitReached notification will be sent

bSWTaskRestartability.name: bSWTaskRestartability
bSWTaskRestartability.description: This indicates whether a process is enabled or not for restart. If enabled the process in context respawns after it has crashed/stopped.

bSWTaskRestartCount.name: bSWTaskRestartCount
bSWTaskRestartCount.description: This indicates the number of times the process has respawned/restarted.

bSysMemUsed.name: bSysMemUsed
bSysMemUsed.description: The amount of physical RAM, in kilobytes, used by the system.

bSysMemFree.name: bSysMemFree
bSysMemFree.description: The amount of physical RAM, in kilobytes, left unused by the system.

bSysTotalCPUUtilAvailable.name: bSysTotalCPUUtilAvailable
bSysTotalCPUUtilAvailable.description: The total CPU utilization available across all CPU cores. The value is maxcores * 100 percentage.

bSysAvgCPUUtil15Sec.name: bSysAvgCPUUtil15Sec
bSysAvgCPUUtil15Sec.description: The average CPU utilization across all CPU cores in the last 15 seconds. This value is updated for every bCPUMonInterval seconds. Units is percentage . Range is from 0 to 100 .

bSysAvgCPUUtil1Min.name: bSysAvgCPUUtil1Min
bSysAvgCPUUtil1Min.description: The average CPU utilization across all CPU cores in the last one minute. This value is updated for every bCPUMonInterval seconds. Units is percentage . Range is from 0 to 100 .

bSysAvgCPUUtil5Min.name: bSysAvgCPUUtil5Min
bSysAvgCPUUtil5Min.description: The average CPU utilization across all CPU cores in the last five minutes. This value is updated for every bCPUMonInterval seconds. Units is percentage . Range is from 0 to 100 .

bCPUMonInterval.name: bCPUMonInterval
bCPUMonInterval.description: CPU usage sampling interval. The value of this object in seconds indicates the how often the CPU utilization is calculated and monitored across all cores. This value for this will be configured by the CLI.

bSWTaskDiedReason.name: bSWTaskDiedReason
bSWTaskDiedReason.description: This indicates the reason for process kill

bSWProcessName.name: bSWProcessName
bSWProcessName.description: The name of the running software task.

bSWProcessAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold.name: bSWProcessAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold
bSWProcessAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold.description: The low threshold for avaerage cpu utilization of a task in a load interval. If a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh event has been generated ( or no bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow was generated previously ) for this task, and the value for average cpu utilization has fallen below the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold, then a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow event will be generated. No more bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow events will be generated for this task until the value for average cpu utilization exceeds the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold. Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold

bSWProcessAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold.name: bSWProcessAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold
bSWProcessAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold.description: The high threshold for average cpu utilization of a task in a load interval. If a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow event has been generated ( or no bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh was generated previously ) for this task, and the value for average cpu utilization has exceeded the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold, then a bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh event will be generated. No more bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh events will be generated for this task until the value for average cpu utilization becomes equal to or less than the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold. Unit is percentage. Range is from 0 to bSWTaskCPUUsageLimit

bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow.name: bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow
bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLow.description: This notification signifies that the average cpu utilization in a load interval is cleared , meaning that it has fallen below the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageLowThreshold for that task bSWTaskName.

bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh.name: bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh
bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHigh.description: This notification signifies that the average cpu utilization in a load interval has risen above the value of bSWTaskAvgCPUUsageHighThreshold for that task bSWTaskName.

bSWTaskDied.name: bSWTaskDied
bSWTaskDied.description: This notification signifies that the process has died. This notification will also be sent if the process manager kills a process because of reaching cpu usage limit or process crashed/terminated

bSWTaskRestartLimitReached.name: bSWTaskRestartLimitReached
bSWTaskRestartLimitReached.description: This notification signifies that the process has reached maximum restarts and all the attempts to restart the process has failed.
